== Other versions of the legendarium ==
In the ''[[The Grey Annals]]'', created in the 1930s,<ref>{{WJ|P1}}, p, 3</ref> Bëor was directly followed by Bregolas and [[Barahir]], who were his sons (and Bregolas was born in {{FA|400}}<ref>{{GA|124}}, p. 49</ref>).  After publication of ''[[The Lord of the Rings]]'' a new genealogy for the [[House of Bëor]] was made in the 1950s and at that time four generations were inserted after Bëor, with Bregor becoming the father of Bregolas and Barahir.<ref>{{WJ|14}}, ''(i) The House of Bëor'', p. 229</ref>

